### Dexie.js Database Declaration and CRUD Operations

Source: https://github.com/dexie/dexie.js/blob/master/samples/vanilla-js/hello-world.html

This snippet demonstrates how to declare a new Dexie.js IndexedDB database, define its schema with a 'friends' store, and then perform common CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations. It includes adding a new record, querying for records based on a condition, and basic error handling using Promises.

```javascript
var db = new Dexie('FriendDatabase');
db.version(1).stores({
  friends: '++id, name, age'
});

db.friends.add({
  name: 'Josephine',
  age: 21
}).then((id) => {
  alert(`Successfully added a friend with id ${id}`);
}).then(() => {
  return db.friends.where('age').below(25).toArray();
}).then((youngFriends) => {
  alert(`My young friends: ${JSON.stringify(youngFriends)}`);
}).catch((error) => {
  alert(`Oops, error: ${error}`);
});
```

